**Sec. 90001. Border Infrastructure and Wall System.**

This section appropriates $46.55 billion for fiscal year 2025 to the Commissioner of U.S. Customs and Border Protection for constructing, installing, or improving new or replacement barriers, including primary, waterborne, and secondary barriers, along the border. The funds will also cover access roads, barrier system attributes like cameras, lights, and sensors, and ground preparation for U.S. Customs and Border Protection operations, with the money remaining available until September 30, 2029.

**Sec. 90002. U.S. Customs and Border Protection Personnel, Fleet Vehicles, and Facilities.**

This section allocates $11.955 billion for fiscal year 2025 to the Commissioner of U.S. Customs and Border Protection for hiring and training additional personnel, providing bonuses, repairing and acquiring patrol vehicles, and improving facilities and checkpoints. The funds will remain available until September 30, 2029, and are specifically restricted from being used to recruit, hire, or train personnel for processing coordinators after October 31, 2028.

**Sec. 90003. Detention Capacity.**

This section appropriates $45 billion for fiscal year 2025 to U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement for single adult alien detention capacity and family residential center capacity, with the funds remaining available until September 30, 2029. It allows for the detention of aliens at family residential centers pending decisions on their removal and sets detention standards at the discretion of the Secretary of Homeland Security.

**Sec. 90004. Border Security, Technology, and Screening.**

This section appropriates $6.168 billion for fiscal year 2025 to the Commissioner of U.S. Customs and Border Protection for enhancing border security through the procurement of new inspection equipment, surveillance technologies, and biometric entry and exit systems. The funds will also cover air and marine operations, screening of persons entering or exiting the United States, and initial screenings of unaccompanied alien children, with the money remaining available until September 30, 2029.

**Sec. 90005. State and Local Assistance.**

This section appropriates $2.575 billion for fiscal year 2025 to the Administrator of the Federal Emergency Management Agency for enhancing state and local security through grants, contracts, and other activities. The funds will support security measures for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, the 2028 Olympics, and the Operation Stonegarden Grant Program, with the money remaining available until September 30, 2029. Additionally, it establishes a $10 billion State Border Security Reinforcement Fund for grants to states and local governments for border security activities.

**Sec. 90006. Presidential Residence Protection.**

This section appropriates $300 million for fiscal year 2025 to the Administrator of the Federal Emergency Management Agency for reimbursing extraordinary law enforcement costs for protecting the President's residences. The funds will cover costs incurred by state or local agencies on or after July 1, 2024, and remain available until September 30, 2029.

**Sec. 90007. Department of Homeland Security Appropriations for Border Support.**

This section appropriates $10 billion for fiscal year 2025 to the Secretary of Homeland Security for reimbursing costs incurred in supporting the Department's mission to safeguard U.S. borders. The funds will remain available until September 30, 2029.

**Sec. 90101. FEHB Improvements.**

This section amends the Federal Employees Health Benefits (FEHB) program to require the Director of the Office of Personnel Management to issue regulations and implement processes for verifying the eligibility of family members added to health benefits plans. It also requires the Director to conduct audits and develop a process for disenrolling ineligible individuals, with funding set aside for these activities.

**Sec. 90102. Pandemic Response Accountability Committee.**

This section appropriates $88 million for fiscal year 2026 to the Pandemic Response Accountability Committee to support oversight of the Coronavirus response and funds provided in this Act or any other Act pertaining to the Coronavirus pandemic. It also amends the CARES Act to extend the committee's authority until 2034.

**Sec. 90103. Appropriation for the Office of Management and Budget.**

This section appropriates $100 million for fiscal year 2025 to the Office of Management and Budget for finding budget and accounting efficiencies in the executive branch, with the funds remaining available until September 30, 2029. [end of text]


